      public void setSize(Animal.Size size)
      Sets the size of the animal. Cats and small dogs are considered adult at 4 years old and senior at 9 years old. Medium dogs are considered adult at 3 years old and senior at 9 years old. Large dogs are considered adult at 3 years old and senior at 6 years old.
      Parameters:
      size - the size of the animal
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if size is null

    • getDaysAvailableForAdoption

      public int getDaysAvailableForAdoption(Date today)
      Returns the number of days the animal has been available for adoption. Returns days in rescue (from dateEnterRescue to today). Returns -1 if animal has been adopted. Throws an IllegalArgumentException if (1) today is null or (2) today is before dateEnterRescue.
      Parameters:
      today - the current date
      Returns:
      the number of days
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if today is invalid
